  <para role="TEXT">The <xi:include href="../entities_en.xml"
  xpointer="ent_Index_Tranche_CDS"
  xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" /> module enables you, on behalf
  of your company, to arrange Index Tranche Credit Default Swaps.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">For basic features common to all modules, such as basic terminology
  and the use of lists and forms, see chapter
  <emphasis>Introduction</emphasis>. For descriptions of functions, see
  chapter <emphasis>Functions</emphasis>.</para>

  <para role="TEXT">This chapter gives detailed descriptions of the input forms used by
  this module, and describes any features specific to this module.</para>

  <section role="ITEM">
    <title>Index Tranche Credit Default Swaps</title>

    <para role="TEXT">There are two types of Index Tranche trades:</para>

    <itemizedlist>
      <listitem>
        <para role="TEXT">Tranche</para>

        <para role="TEXT">Tranches are parts of the index trade where you evaluate and do
        trades based on the number of defaults in the index. You can base your
        evaluation on the actual number of trades or a percentage.</para>
      </listitem>

      <listitem>
        <para role="TEXT">Number to Default (NTD)</para>

        <para role="TEXT">A Tranche/N2D Index Credit Derivative Swap (CDS) is a CDS where
        the underlying Index Credit Entity (CE) is linked to a standard or
        customized (off-market) loss or NTD Tranche that allows you to create
        a "leverage" effect.</para>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
  </section>

